{"type": "article", "id": 41977, "title": "专为更衣设计的连衣裙 Undress，换泳装再不愁｜这个设计了不起", "description": "我们每天都为你推荐几个最近发现的好设计。", "date": "2017-06-14T23:26:43Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 41448, "name": "Superposition Studio"}, {"id": 41449, "name": "Another Human"}, {"id": 961, "name": "Hampton Creek"}, {"id": 41450, "name": "Yoni Alter"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 7, "praise_count": 107, "image": "img/article/article_show/2017061507263574XIjldeUWJBgDfi.png", "contents": "<p nocleanhtml=\"true\">        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} p.p3 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p4 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} </style>  </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。</p><h3>Leaded Lights by Superposition Studio</h3><p>以互动体验设计见长的荷兰设计工作室 <a href=\"https://superposition.cc/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Superposition Studio</a> 最近为奈梅亨市 Nimma 酒店的前台设计了一个名为 Leaded Lights 的模块化灯光装置，利用数码技术重新诠释传统的彩绘玻璃。整个装置由 LED 屏、网格状的隔层以及玻璃屏组成，配套的电脑系统会从数据库中摘取新闻显示在屏幕上。根据时间和天气，信息出现的方式和颜色也会作出相应的调整。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614224603dpQX5EPKtYJWwfRm.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614224602if8HIqVoXcC45wQM.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614224602q4Fwlu5aI17fjhvX.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614224603mKsyVl4dG0gWrLY1.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666259\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Undress V3</h3><p>带上运动装或是泳装外出玩耍时，你有没有因为找不到更衣场所不得不尴尬地将自己裹在毛巾里换装的经历？为了让女性能够在公共场合自由且快速地换装，来自美国加州的设计公司于 2014 年推出了一条专为更衣设计的连衣裙 Undress，使用时只要将它穿过内衣，穿在需要脱去的衣服下，就可以迅速地更换上衣和下装了。最近，设计团队又推出了第三代 Undress，新增了和泳装类似的内置胸垫，允许用户大大方方地将它穿在身上，不用担心走光问题。这是它的<a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/denniscaco/the-undress-version-3\" rel=\"nofollow\">众筹链接</a>，售价从 69 美元起。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614224623oGfO3qHYJLZx8FSh.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.857143\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614224623cBCuXiZhvRKztpmq.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.857143\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614224623l5cd0S7QaN2Jie1n.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Convergence Puzzle by Yoni Alter</h3><p>仔细观察这块色彩斑斓的拼图，你有没有发现它其实构成了一幅航拍照？这个名为 Convergence 的拼图是伦敦设计师 <a href=\"http://www.yoniishappy.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Yoni Alter</a> 以纽约曼哈顿东区一处十字路口的航拍为灵感设计的，它的底座由一片单独的木块经 CNC 雕刻而成，Alter 还负责了底座和拼板的上色。毕业于伦敦艺术大学的 Alter 经常从城市中获得启发，除了仅此一份、售价高达 3000 英镑的<a href=\"http://shop.yoniishappy.com/product/convergence-puzzle\" rel=\"nofollow\">手工拼图</a>之外，他还推出了描绘地标性建筑的城市海报系列 Shape of Cities。你可以通过<a href=\"http://shop.yoniishappy.com/products\" rel=\"nofollow\">链接</a>购买到他的作品。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614224634iInJT3xYrjBpbc6V.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614224634OMhuK28TDaQnqXR9.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614224634YoDUB7E0vqrGgLjJ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Another Human by Leah Ring</h3><p>洛杉矶设计师 Leah Ring 以“挑战传统造型与材质”为宗旨创立了一间名为 <a href=\"https://www.anotherhuman.la/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Another Human</a> 的设计工作室，并在纽约设计周期间展示独立工作室作品的 <a href=\"http://offsite.sightunseen.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sight Unseen OFFSITE</a> 上，首次公开了这些怪异又充满趣味的产品：比如把石头当作支架的镜子系列 Aura；由黑色的圆弧构成的 Tubular 杂志架；由几何图形构成、借鉴孟菲斯风格的蓝色衣帽架 Just Cant；模仿冥想石设计的天鹅绒坐垫。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614225211AtzgTLo0hCMEBykr.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"medium-insert-image-active\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"medium-insert-caption-placeholder\"></figcaption></figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614225211uXaLKSOHeGv58txz.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614225211y0dSZVqHx5pJ216G.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614225212PlpH8LVmkoEbh2BW.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.800000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Hampton Creek</h3><p>为了挑战市场对于健康、可持续产品的固有印象，高科技食品公司 <a href=\"http://www.eatjust.com/en-us\" rel=\"nofollow\">Hampton Creek</a> 最近用一组简洁明了的摄影替换了旗下标志性的棕色标签。设计团队根据每款色拉酱的风味和酱料常见的蔬菜搭配，拍摄了一组抹开的色拉酱和对应的菜叶，借此强调产品的纯粹与天然。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614224708gIAEPqpcdlBhOSxF.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562500\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201706142247085PfymeAVu9GBrhSk.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.587500\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614224709c4yNnoQ92KjtpPzq.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Wood Sculptures by Keisuke Tanaka</h3><p>用“看得见风景的画框”来形容日本艺术家<a href=\"http://www.yamamotogendai.org/japanese/artists/keisuke-tanaka\" rel=\"nofollow\">田中圭介</a>创作的木雕或许再确切不过了，他擅于在废弃的木料上细心地雕刻出迷你的自然景观。除了画框之外，他还创作了一组名为 Next Cloth 的雕塑，乍看之下还以为它们是皱成一团的真实布料。这些充满自然气息的作品最近正在东京 <a href=\"http://www.spiral.co.jp/en/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Spiral</a> 举行的 <a href=\"http://www.spiral.co.jp/en/e_schedule/detail_2266.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">WONDERS</a> 展上展出，将持续至 6 月 18 日。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614224722h1PJVcwQNIM5lRAi.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.499118\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614224722yXBEfMua8tVpZiPo.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667059\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614224723GUR4WuxviN3IHmw6.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.683529\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170614224723kX4mHLOxweayZcio.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667059\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}